reviewText: Funny, funny, very enjoyable though there is strong language. Chris Rock is a very good actor that can carry this extreme type of funny off without it not being a good story as well.

A great film. It has everything you hope for. It is clever, well-written, super acting, and it is a feel good comedy with a message. You will walk around saying "That ain''t right!" for a while. Chris Rock is one of our premiere comedic talents and we are blessed to have him! Somehow, he tells it like it really is - both on stage - and in this great movie. Bernie Mac is hilarious, too - one of the elder statesmen that Rock may have learned from. Anyway, they really dominate and take no prisoners in "Head of State" which neither my spouse or I had ever heard of. What a shame! Anyway, definitely see this one. It is just so, so good.

Had this movie been made after 2008 Chris Rock would have been bashed for insulting President Obama.  What is uncanny is that 5 years before Obama ran for president, Chris Rock did a movie that comedically explores many of the racial dynamics of an African American POTUS.

Great comedy.  I really enjoyed this movie.

Head of State is very funny and appropriate.  Chris Rock and Bernie Mac together is comedy genius at its best.  The two comedians play well off of one another. The subliminal messages and outright in-your-face messages of the first black president is remarkable.  It's weird - the first time I saw this movie years ago it was okay.  Recently,  I saw the movie again and was laughing outloud.  Which is why I purchased the DVD.  Great movie.  Chris Rock and Bernie Mac two of the greatest of all time.
